The White House has released the first-ever comprehensive National Action Plan to Combat Human Trafficking. This plan is based on the three pillars of prevention, protection, and prosecution, as outlined in the Trafficking Victims Protection Act of 2000. The plan also emphasizes the importance of collaborative and cooperative efforts among various stakeholders and professionals. The Trump Administration is committed to addressing human trafficking, supporting victims, and holding traffickers accountable. The National Action Plan, along with an Executive Summary and One Page Brief, can be accessed through the provided link.